This is one of the top restaurants in San Francisco for a reason. You know it is when Kendrick Lamar comes in town to dine here. There's breakfast, lunch and dinner items and the concept here is to mesh French, creole and southern dishes together. The restaurant is pretty small with several white-clothed tables in the center of the room, and small tables in the window and small tables throughout the restaurant. Interior displays an artistic vibe. Customer favorite items include the beignets(fried doughnuts), grillades (beef cutlet in gravy), andouilles, and more. Workers here were all super friendly and provided high quality service. Food rundown...beignets. Try that definitely. There are four different kinds to choose from: plain, chocolate with molten Ghirardelli, Granny Smith apple with cinnamon-honey butter, and a crawfish that is spiced with cayenne, scallions & cheddar. If you cant seem to decide on which one, you can order a flight which is one of each. These are pretty big sized so they're great for sharing! These fried doughnuts are very thick and doughy but my absolute favorite would be the crawfish. Too much cayenne but with a rich, cheesy flavor. The egg Benedict? Cheat meal. Cajun hollandaise sauce topped it well. Chicken was very crispy on the outside but lacked flavor. The biscuit was a bit dry. Overall, 4 stars.

Overall, Brenda's is a great spot. I've had other things on their menu, but nothing has ever stood out. The other beignets (apple and chocolate) are pretty meh as well.     Brenda's is a pretty hit or miss sometimes, but I've definitely had more misses. There's usually always a line during brunch hours on the weekends, so expect to wait at least 90mins before getting seated if you're writing your name down.

    On my most recent visit, a Wednesday afternoon, there was no line! After looking at the menu, my friend and I decided to get the crawfish beignets, the plain beignets, the hangtown fry (with hash and a biscuit) and a cafe au lait. Our food came out fairly quickly. The hangtown fry was okay, maybe I just don't like oysters but it was meh, but hash and biscuit were really good though!

    The crawfish beignets were really good! I'm a big fan of them here and I love how flavorful they are and how they're fried perfectly. I do have to say there isn't much crawfish in then.

    My favorites were the plain beignets though! They were fried perfectly and I love the generous amounts of powdered sugar on top. I love dipping them with the cafe au lait - brings me back to my time in NOLA at Cafe du Monde! Highly recommend.

    Overall, Brenda's is a great spot. I've had other things on their menu, but nothing has ever stood out. The other beignets (apple and chocolate) are pretty meh as well. I would say Brenda's is pretty overhyped, but I do come here once in a while..however, this spot is definitely not worth the wait.

    5/7/2019

    Finally came here on my vacation after having it on my bookmark for a few years. Yelp came through again, this place is legit.

    After some research, my friend and I ordered:

    1.) Fried chicken eggs benedict. (Was deciding between fried chicken or fried catfish. I would bet both are good so just decide on preference.)

    2.) Grit and Shrimp.

    3.) Beignet flight.

    4.) Gumbo. (Almost didn't order this because we were afraid we couldn't finish all the food. Very glad we did order it, please do the same.)

    5.) Watermelon house iced tea. (Almost didn't order this, but so glad I did.)

    Every single dish was great. My personal favorite gotta be the gumbo. The chicken was cooked perfect, not dry at all.

    Service was as good as it gets. Very, very fast and attentive. I was very impressed. The food all came out within 5 minutes!

    I will bring my all my friends, including those from out of town, to this restaurant in the future.

    Pretty good breakfast/brunch joint. I've been here a couple times on my trips to SF and everytime the food has been good.

    Favorites are their Fried Chicken Benedict... The chicken is moist and nicely fried. Also the crawfish beignet is very good. I personally prefer it over their dessert beignets. Definitely try!

    There has always been a wait for me. You put your name down on the big chalk blackboard.

    We parked meter on the street but apparently there are free street parking also available if you look around.
